Hello again, you scrolled down to the description of me. About two years ago, I decided to try myself as a Frontend Developer. I like to solve unusual tasks, I easily find a common language with new people, for me the main goal is self-improvement, it is important to become and know that you are better than yesterday. I have various skills and hobbies: I read books, go in for sports, try Photoshop, play and learn to develop games.

As a result, after minimal training, I got involved and continued to study even more, took developer courses at the RS School, and gained a lot of experience and made many projects. At the moment I am looking for a company that can show that I am capable of much.
